reviews_data.review_text:
My boyfriend and I had an amazing experience here!
We visited for breakfast last weekend from out of town. We were staying at a hotel nearby, and decided to get breakfast before heading home.
We were immediately impressed with the decor and interior design. There are many different types of seating to suit any customer. You have the option to experience the authenticity of a more middle eastern seating arrangement or a more westernized one. I enjoyed both the table and chairs that sit in an Americanized way as well as the ones seated lower to the ground. They served us at our table we chose with ease.
The display of baked goods was immaculate and enticing. It was difficult to choose what we wanted, as everything looked amazing. They have a video display viewable on at least two screens where you can watch some of their dishes on the menu being made.
For breakfast my boyfriend ordered an egg and cheese biscuit which came with pickles and kettle chips. We believe the pickles were likely made in house or they are a specific brand, as they tasted of a unique seasoning blend. To drink, he ordered a shaken espresso. We both tasted it, and were very impressed with the flavor. I ordered mini pancakes without banana. They were the perfect consistency, and had a sauce that seemed to be similar to Nutella on top, what I believe were cashews, and strawberries. For my drink, I ordered a matcha Frappuccino. It was possibly the best I’ve had in my life.
We had gotten both drinks and my boyfriend’s meal, but were waiting on mine. One of the servers noticed, and went to check on it. She was very apologetic about my waiting, but I was enjoying the ambiance and overall experience. She returned, again very apologetic, stating that my ticket had been misplaced and they would have it out to me very soon. It had gotten very busy immediately after we placed our order, and I was more than willing to forgive waiting a bit longer. The staff was very patient, kind, apologetic, and did their best to provide the best service they could. When the server returned with my meal, she brought us two small desserts for our wait. I feel they more than made up for the minor mistake.
Everything we had was incredibly delectable. It was such a wonderful experience overall that I quite literally shed tears. I’ve never had such an enjoyable experience.
We decided to order once more before leaving. We placed a to-go order for a mixed berry tart, baklava cheesecake, and two refreshers. I had the dragonfruit lychee refresher, and my boyfriend ordered the watermelon kiwi. Both were incredible.
We intend to visit any and every time we are in Charlotte going forward.
If they ever decide to expand toward the Asheville/Weaverville area we would be inclined to be regulars.

reviews_data.review_text:
My boyfriend and I had an amazing experience here!
We visited for breakfast last weekend from out of town. We were staying at a hotel nearby, and decided to get breakfast before heading home.
We were immediately impressed with the decor and interior design. There are many different types of seating to suit any customer. You have the option to experience the authenticity of a more middle eastern seating arrangement or a more westernized one. I enjoyed both the table and chairs that sit in an Americanized way as well as the ones seated lower to the ground. They served us at our table we chose with ease.
The display of baked goods was immaculate and enticing. It was difficult to choose what we wanted, as everything looked amazing. They have a video display viewable on at least two screens where you can watch some of their dishes on the menu being made.
For breakfast my boyfriend ordered an egg and cheese biscuit which came with pickles and kettle chips. We believe the pickles were likely made in house or they are a specific brand, as they tasted of a unique seasoning blend. To drink, he ordered a shaken espresso. We both tasted it, and were very impressed with the flavor. I ordered mini pancakes without banana. They were the perfect consistency, and had a sauce that seemed to be similar to Nutella on top, what I believe were cashews, and strawberries. For my drink, I ordered a matcha Frappuccino. It was possibly the best I’ve had in my life.
We had gotten both drinks and my boyfriend’s meal, but were waiting on mine. One of the servers noticed, and went to check on it. She was very apologetic about my waiting, but I was enjoying the ambiance and overall experience. She returned, again very apologetic, stating that my ticket had been misplaced and they would have it out to me very soon. It had gotten very busy immediately after we placed our order, and I was more than willing to forgive waiting a bit longer. The staff was very patient, kind, apologetic, and did their best to provide the best service they could. When the server returned with my meal, she brought us two small desserts for our wait. I feel they more than made up for the minor mistake.
Everything we had was incredibly delectable. It was such a wonderful experience overall that I quite literally shed tears. I’ve never had such an enjoyable experience.
We decided to order once more before leaving. We placed a to-go order for a mixed berry tart, baklava cheesecake, and two refreshers. I had the dragonfruit lychee refresher, and my boyfriend ordered the watermelon kiwi. Both were incredible.
We intend to visit any and every time we are in Charlotte going forward.
If they ever decide to expand toward the Asheville/Weaverville area we would be inclined to be regulars.

reviews_data.review_text: Finally I got to step into  the most anticipated Vavela Café. I felt like walking into a piece of Istanbul, where time slows down and every sip tells a story. The Turkish coffee sade arrived sans foam which confused me  still it had a rich aroma swirling like whispers from the Grand Bazaar. Each sip was deep and velvety, leaving a warm, lingering spice on my anxious palate. REMEMBER NO STIRRING. The Turkish cake, adorned with delicate pistachios, was soft and fragrant, like something a sultan’s chef might serve in a palace garden. Now for the atmosphere it's glowing with highlights and lowlights elevating decor, truly a an exotic carpet ride. The natural light compliments the rooms charm—golden lights, cozy seating, and music that feels like a gentle breeze from the Bosphorus. Now the critique: absence of water was my fault invaluable to cleanse my palate and signature dark cloud of foam. Lastly ,my  staff members limited knowledge or interest in Turkish coffee traditions, took away some authenticity, though the ambiance remained. I will venture to say it will be a Charlotte favorite for a long time. And I will return to this café whenever I crave a taste of Turkey’s soul.~Rainni

Looking forward to welcoming you back for many more “exotic carpet rides” and authentic moments. See you soon!
